race.comment: A good race. SCHEELITE (3) returned from a spell beaten 2.7L over 1440m at Caulfield when expected to need the outing. Had come off close-up efforts in Stake and Group company and is proven second-up. Maps well and at best is well-placed to be winning. PRESSER (7) brings a string of placings from decent metro contests, and the on-pacer improved again at Moonee Valley last time over this distance. Should enjoy a soft run and is feared. THE CREATOR (6) is a leader who ran strong relative numbers twice at The Valley before folding up at Caulfield. Connections believe he performs best with the sting out of the surface and he's been freshened. Monitor conditions on the day. HOWLIN' RAIN (5) needed the first-up outing at Caulfield but will be much more competitive today. An each-way proposition if presented on song.
